"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-nepal-outcast-from-olympic-qualifier-after-losing-to-india-1-3\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, April 6: A 3-1 defeat against India means that Nepal's women's national football team will not be able to qualify for the 2020 Summer Olympics in Japan.  Nepal's defeat to India is its second consecutive loss. Earlier, Nepal was defeated 3-1 by the host nation, Myanmar. Nepal will now play against Indonesia, its last group stage game on Tuesday.  Nepal, India, Indonesia and Myanmar were in Group A. On November 2018, Nepal had qualified for the second round after a 1-1 draw against Bangladesh, India and Myanmar. Nepal managed to set its place into the second phase of qualification as top three teams from the group.  The 5th edition of the AFC Women's Olympic Qualifying Tournament, the quadrennial international football competition is organized by the Asian Football Confederation (AFC) to select women national teams from Asia for the Olympic football tournament.  The top two teams of the tournament will qualify for the 2020 Summer Olympics women's football tournament in Japan as the AFC representatives, together with Japan which is already qualified for the Olympics as the host nation.    Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (im